          "body": "John's stated purpose (20:30-31) is that *these have been written so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that believing you may have life in His name*. John 2 establishes the pattern by which his readers will be brought to that belief: through signs that disclose glory, interpreted by Scripture and remembered post-resurrection, received by disciples whose faith Jesus accepts — and warned against by the example of crowd-faith that goes no deeper than the spectacle. The chapter's two signs together teach what saving faith requires: not merely that something happens, but that we receive *Jesus Himself* as the One in whom these things are true."
